<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15063d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15063d">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15063d"> 63(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> uccello, auspicia</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Che l&apos;imperio della Scizia era suo; perch&egrave; ivi esso aveva gli <mark>auspicj</mark>; talch&egrave; per l&apos;<mark>uccello</mark> d&apos;Idantura, un re eroico di Grecia arebbe mandato a Dario due ale; un re eroico latino gli arebbe risposto, <i>auspicia esse sua</i>. <br><font color="green">[That the empire of Scythia was his because he possessed its <mark>auspices</mark>. Thus where a heroic king of Greece would have sent Darius two wings in place of Idanthyrsus&apos; <mark>bird</mark>, a heroic Latin king would have replied <i>auspicia esse sua</i> [&lsquo;that the auspices belonged to him&rsquo;.]</font> <small> Giovanni Battista Vico, <a name="VICO2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#VICO2"><cite title="source">Principes de la philosophe de l'histoire</cite></a> (edition unknown) III</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15239d" href="c15all.htm#c15239d">VI.C.15:239(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
